Package edu.first.robot

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    RobotMode
    The framework for all "modes" a robot can perform, this is the basic class that tells the robot what it should do and when it should do it.
    RobotModeSelector
    Interface to represent something that can select a robot mode.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    IterativeRobot
    Main class representing an "iterative" style robot mode.
    IterativeRobotAdapter
    An adapter pattern class for robot modes that are iterative, but do not use all methods in the IterativeRobot class.
    RobotModeSendableChooser
    A SendableChooser class meant to provide a safe environment to select a RobotMode from SmartDashboard.
    SafeRobotMode
    An implementation of RobotMode that catches all exceptions in every method.
    SimpleRobot
    Main class representing a "Simple" style robot mode.
    SimpleRobotAdapter
    An adapter pattern class for robot modes that use the SimpleRobot class, but do not need to use all of its methods.
